				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\Phi }_{k}$$\end{document} indicates the maintenance factor (herein 1.06), whereas N is the annual plant operating hours (i.e., 8000 h). Moreover, CRF in previous equation indicates the capital recovery factor as determined by Eq. (13) (Bejan et al. 1996):13CRF=i×(1+i)n(1+i)n-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
