The exergoenvironmental factor is a valuable benchmark expressed as the ratio of the environmental impact of the equipment unit to its total environmental impact accounting for the construction to destruction process. Therefore, a factor close to one in Eq. (24) indicates that the current environmental impact of the equipment is more significant than the environmental impact of its destruction (Cavalcanti 2017).24fb,k=Y˙kY˙k+bf,k·E˙xD,k\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
